
[1]gnomiometrical

   GNOMIOMET'RICAL, a. [Gr. an index, and to measure.]

   The gnomiometrical telescope and microscope is an instrument for
   measuring the angles of crystals by reflection, and for ascertaining
   the inclination of strata, and the apparaent magnitude of angles when
   the eye is not placed at the vertex.
